    <body xml:id="Document"><div type="chapter" xml:id="Ch92" n="92"><pb type="VIII_2" n="731"/><head>92.
DE MOTU PERPETUO 1</head>
<head>1674 und Mai 1678</head><div type="ueberlieferung"><p><hi rendition="#b #smaller">Überlieferung:</hi>
<list><item><label><hi rendition="#i #smaller">L</hi></label>
<p><hi rendition="#smaller">Konzept:
LH XXXVII 5 Bl. 57.
1 Bl. 4<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi>. 2 S.</hi></p><p><hi rendition="#smaller">Cc 2, Nr. 836</hi></p></item></list></p></div><div type="text"><p xml:id="Ch92.p1" rendition="#noindent"><pb type="L"/><fw type="folNum">[57 r<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi>]</fw> 1674. Parisiis.<lb/>Totum continuandi Motus <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main">artificium in eo consistit,</lem><note type="lemma-abbrev">artificium</note><rdg wit="#L" n="1"> est, </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="2"> in eo consistit, <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg></app> ut inveniatur ratio restituendi vim restituentem<index indexName="Sachverzeichnis"><term>vis restituens</term></index>, aliunde quam per restituendam. Itaque duae vires ita inter se invicem applicandae sunt, ut vis restituens rem suam agat separatim, compensatis omnibus, sans interesser
la machine. Hoc vero admirabili quadam ratione, sic fieri potest:</p><p xml:id="Ch92.p2">Esto canalis <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m1"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula> mobilis circa centrum in medio <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m2"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math></formula> quod tubum in duas dividit partes communicationem inter se non habentes. <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main">Medietates <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m3"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>,</lem><note type="lemma-abbrev">Medietates</note><rdg wit="#L" n="1"> <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m4"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula> </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="2"> <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m5"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>, <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg></app> <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m6"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula> subsectae sunto in duas partes aequales <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m7"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>D</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m8"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>, vel <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m9"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>E</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m10"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula> in punctis <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m11"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>D</m:mi></m:math></formula>, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m12"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>E</m:mi></m:math></formula>. Mobiles sint in
<app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main">canali globi duo sic satis ponderosi, globus <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m13"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>F</m:mi></m:math></formula></lem><note type="lemma-abbrev">canali</note><rdg wit="#L" n="1"> pondera duo, pondus </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="2"> globi <seg type="apparat-ellipsis"/> globus <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m14"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>F</m:mi></m:math></formula>
<hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg></app><index indexName="Sachverzeichnis"><term>globus</term></index> in medietate <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m15"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>, globus</lem><note type="lemma-abbrev"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m16"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>,</note><rdg wit="#L" n="1"> pondus </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="2"> globus <hi rendition="#i">L</hi> </rdg></app> autem <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m17"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>G</m:mi></m:math></formula> in medietate</lem><note type="lemma-abbrev"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m18"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>G</m:mi></m:math></formula></note><rdg wit="#L" n="1"> in ponder </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="2"> in medietate <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg></app> <formula xml:id="Ch92.p2.m19"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>.<!--  \hack{\newline\hspace*{7,5mm}} 
     \hackfor{\par}--></p><p xml:id="Ch92.p3">Ex punctis <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m1"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>D</m:mi></m:math></formula>, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m2"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>E</m:mi></m:math></formula> descendant pondera<index indexName="Sachverzeichnis"><term>pondus</term></index> <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m3"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>H</m:mi></m:math></formula>, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m4"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:math></formula> lineis rigidis <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main"><!--is-addition-app-with-lemma--><add resp="#L">sive regulis</add></lem><note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg. L</hi></note></app> <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m5"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>D</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>H</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m6"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula> circa centra, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m7"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>D</m:mi></m:math></formula>, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m8"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>E</m:mi></m:math></formula>, mobilibus affixa. Quodlibet horum ponderum <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m9"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>H</m:mi></m:math></formula>, <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m10"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:math></formula> Elaterium<index indexName="Sachverzeichnis"><term>elaterium</term></index> in spiram<index indexName="Sachverzeichnis"><term>spira</term></index> si placet convolutum gestet; tantarumque sit virium pondus ut dum machina<index indexName="Sachverzeichnis"><term>machina</term></index> ex situ <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m11"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula> versus situm <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m12"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></formula></lem><note type="lemma-abbrev"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m13"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula></note><rdg wit="#L" n="1"> in </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="2"> versus situm <app><rdg wit="#L" n="a"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m14"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>L</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula> </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="b"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m15"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></formula> <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg></app></rdg></app> <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main">tendit in situm <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m16"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></formula> ⟨ob pondus⟩ <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m17"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>G</m:mi></m:math></formula> remotiorem in centro quam <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m18"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>F</m:mi></m:math></formula>, tunc pondus <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m19"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:math></formula> nisu</lem><note type="lemma-abbrev">tendit</note><rdg wit="#L" n="1"> <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m20"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:math></formula> scilicet tendente in <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m21"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math></formula> pondus nisu suo <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m22"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:math></formula>, </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="2"> ob pondus <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m23"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>G</m:mi></m:math></formula> remotius a centro quam <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m24"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>F</m:mi></m:math></formula>, pondus nisu suo <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m25"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:math></formula> </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="3"> in situm <seg type="apparat-ellipsis"/> nisu suo <hi rendition="#i">L</hi> </rdg></app> suo contra canalem rigidum <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m26"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></formula>, cui scilicet inter descendendum appropinquat, spiram suam nullo negotio involvat in se, sive tendat. At ubi in situm perpendicularem <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m27"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></formula> vel paulo citeriorem</lem><note type="lemma-abbrev"><formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m28"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>⁢</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></formula></note><rdg wit="#L" n="1"> paulo scilicet </rdg><rdg wit="#L" n="2"> vel paulo citeriorem <hi rendition="#i">L</hi></rdg></app> aut (ob accelerationem<index indexName="Sachverzeichnis"><term>acceleratio</term></index> descensus <app type="Bfootnote"><lem type="main"><!--is-addition-app-with-lemma--><add resp="#L">si nullo alio motu oneretur</add></lem><note type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">erg. L</hi></note></app>) paulo ulteriorem, pervenerit, liberetur spira (impactu quodam aliterve, cessante si placet contactu canalis). Seque restituens pondus <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m29"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>G</m:mi></m:math></formula> nunc translatum in locum <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m30"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mi>G</m:mi></m:math></formula>, inde sursum pellat in locum <formula xml:id="Ch92.p3.m31"><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>G</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></formula>.</p><pb type="VIII_2" n="732"/><figure rendition="#own-line_centered" xml:id="Ch92.p4">
